The Beck family eagerly set out to harvest disease-free oysters from managed reserves after years of waiting for them to grow to legal size.
Meanwhile, debates continue over introducing Asian oysters to the Chesapeake Bay to revive the declining native oyster population.
Concerns about pollution and sewage runoff further complicate the bay's restoration efforts.
Despite challenges, oysters remain a symbol of hope and tradition along the bay's shores, with businesses like Harris's continuing to honor and serve them.
The future of the bay's ecosystem hangs in the balance as stakeholders navigate complex environmental and economic issues.
